   "source": [
    "# Linear Bivariate BMM with SAMBA toy models : switchcos mixing\n",
    "\n",
    "The best way to learn Taweret is to use it. You can run, modify and experiment with this notebook [GitHub Codespaces](https://github.com/bandframework/Taweret)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "economic-dublin",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This notebook try to reproduce the work by **A. C. Semposki, R. J. Furnstahl, D. R. Phillips** in  [Uncertainties here, there, and everywhere: interpolating between small- and large-g expansions using Bayesian Model Mixing](https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.04116) using the Bayesian model mixing package **Taweret**. \n",
    "\n",
    "**Author : Dan Liyanage**\n",
    "\n",
    "Date : 11/10/2022\n",
    "\n",
    "More about SAMBA toy models can be found in [Uncertainties here, there, and everywhere: interpolating between small- and large-g expansions using Bayesian Model Mixing](https://arxiv.org/abs/2206.04116)\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "favorite-fancy",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "**Steps for Bayesian Model Mixing with Taweret**\n",
    "\n",
    "    1. Define your models using BayesModel class in `Taweret.core.bayesmodel` (Only if you want to bring in your own models)\n",
    "    2. Choose a Mixing method (Avilable mixing methods can be found in Taweret/mix)\n",
    "    3. Find the posterior for the mixture weights (parameters in the mixture function) and/or model parameters by training the mixed model. \n",
    "    4. Make predictions! "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "after-peace",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "import os\n",
    "\n",
    "# You will have to change the following imports depending on where you have \n",
    "# the packages installed\n",
    "\n",
    "cwd = os.getcwd()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Get the first part of this path and append to the sys.path\n",
    "tw_path = cwd.split(\"Taweret/\")[0] + \"Taweret\"\n",
    "sys.path.append(tw_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# For plotting\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "sns.set_context('poster')\n",
    "# To define priors. (uncoment if not using default priors)\n",
    "import bilby\n",
    "\n",
    "# For other operations\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c33c9f9f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Get toy models and the pseudo-experimental data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "loaded-machinery",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Toy models from SAMBA\n",
    "from Taweret.models import samba_models as toy_models\n",
    "\n",
    "m1 = toy_models.Loworder(2, 'uninformative')\n",
    "m2 = toy_models.Highorder(2, 'uninformative')\n",
    "truth = toy_models.TrueModel()\n",
    "exp = toy_models.Data()\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "lasting-spokesman",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "g = np.linspace(0.1, 0.6, 10)\n",
    "plot_g = np.linspace(0.01,1,100)\n",
    "m1_prediction = m1.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "m2_prediction = m2.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "true_output = truth.evaluate(plot_g)\n",
    "exp_data= exp.evaluate(g,error = 0.01)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "dimensional-greene",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<matplotlib.legend.Legend at 0x155d0b550>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "\n",
    "fig, ax_f = plt.subplots(figsize=(10,10))\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, m1_prediction[0].flatten(), label='low order')\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, m2_prediction[0].flatten(), label='high order')\n",
    "ax_f.plot(plot_g, true_output[0], label='truth')\n",
    "ax_f.scatter(g,exp_data[0], marker='x', label='experimental data')\n",
    "ax_f.set_ylim(1.2,3.2)\n",
    "ax_f.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "limited-application",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "###  2. Choose a Mixing method"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "thorough-exercise",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "switchcos mixing function has 3                   free parameter(s)\n",
      "Warning : Default prior is set to {'switchcos_0': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_0', latex_label='switchcos_0', unit=None, boundary=None), 'switchcos_1': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_1', latex_label='switchcos_1', unit=None, boundary=None), 'switchcos_2': Uniform(minimum=0, maximum=1, name='switchcos_2', latex_label='switchcos_2', unit=None, boundary=None)}\n",
      "To change the prior use `set_prior` method\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Mixing method\n",
    "from Taweret.mix.bivariate_linear import BivariateLinear as BL\n",
    "\n",
    "models= {'low_order':m1,'high_order':m2}\n",
    "mix_model = BL(models_dic=models, method='switchcos') "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f32d8cc2",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#####  Need to speceify a constained prior for switchcos. g1 < g3 < g2\n",
    "We follow Bilby documentation on how to specefy a prior with constraints\n",
    "https://lscsoft.docs.ligo.org/bilby/prior.html#prior-constraints"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "bcbf725e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# from scipy import stats \n",
    "\n",
    "# def luniform(theta, a, b):\n",
    "\n",
    "#     if theta > a and theta < b:\n",
    "#         return 0.0\n",
    "#     else:\n",
    "#         return -np.inf\n",
    "\n",
    "# def lpdf(params):\n",
    "#     if len(params) == 3:\n",
    "#         #g1 truncated between (0, 0.35) \n",
    "#         g1 = luniform(params[0], 0.01, 0.3) + stats.norm.logpdf(params[0], 0.1, 0.05)   #0.1 for 2 v 2, #0.1 for 5 v 5\n",
    "#         #g3 truncated between (g1, 0.35)\n",
    "#         g3 = luniform(params[2], params[0], 0.55) + stats.norm.logpdf(params[2], 0.4, 0.05)   #0.4 for 2 v 2, #0.25 for 5 v 5\n",
    "#         #g2 truncated between (g3, 0.35)\n",
    "#         g2 = luniform(params[1], params[2], 0.8) + stats.norm.logpdf(params[1], 0.6, 0.05)  #0.6 for 2 v 2, #0.4 for 5 v 5\n",
    "#         return (g1 + g2 + g3)\n",
    "#     else:\n",
    "#         print(params)\n",
    "#         raise ValueError('The number of parameters does not match any available switching function.')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "a32b6e23",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from bilby.core.prior.joint import BaseJointPriorDist, JointPrior, JointPriorDistError\n",
    "from Taweret.utils.priors import Priors as samba_P\n",
    "samba_prior = samba_P()\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "class custom_prior_switchcos(BaseJointPriorDist):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, names, bounds=None):\n",
    "        '''\n",
    "        A class defining prior for swithcos mixing method\n",
    "\n",
    "        Parameters\n",
    "        ==========\n",
    "        names: list\n",
    "            A list of the parameter names in the prior\n",
    "        '''\n",
    "        super().__init__(names=names, bounds=bounds)\n",
    "        self.names=names\n",
    "    def ln_prob(self,value):\n",
    "        try:\n",
    "            n_sam = value.shape[1]\n",
    "            return [samba_prior.lpdf(x) for x in value]\n",
    "        except:\n",
    "            return samba_prior.lpdf(value)\n",
    "\n",
    "    def _sample(self, size, **kwargs):\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        Draw, and set, a sample for the switchcos parameter joint distribution\n",
    "\n",
    "        Parameters\n",
    "        ==========\n",
    "        size: int\n",
    "            number of samples to generate, defaults to 1\n",
    "        \"\"\"\n",
    "        samps = np.zeros((size, len(self)))\n",
    "        samps[:,0] = np.random.uniform(0.12, 0.18, size)\n",
    "        samps[:,2] = np.random.uniform(0.19, 0.24, size)\n",
    "        samps[:,1] = np.random.uniform(0.25, 0.30, size)\n",
    "\n",
    "        return samps\n",
    "\n",
    "class prior_switchcos(JointPrior):\n",
    "    def __init__(self, dist, name=None, latex_label=None, unit=None):\n",
    "        if not isinstance(dist, custom_prior_switchcos):\n",
    "            raise JointPriorDistError(\"dist object must be instance of custom_prior_switchcos\")\n",
    "        super().__init__(dist=dist, name=name, latex_label=latex_label, unit=unit)\n",
    "\n",
    "mvg = custom_prior_switchcos(names=['switchcos_0', 'switchcos_1', 'switchcos_2'], bounds=[[0.0,0.35],[0.0,0.35],[0.0,0.35]])\n",
    "priors = bilby.core.prior.PriorDict()\n",
    "priors['switchcos_0'] = prior_switchcos(mvg,'switchcos_0')\n",
    "priors['switchcos_1'] = prior_switchcos(mvg,'switchcos_1')\n",
    "priors['switchcos_2'] = prior_switchcos(mvg,'switchcos_2')\n"
   ]
  },

       " 'switchcos_1': __main__.prior_switchcos(dist=custom_prior_switchcos(names=['switchcos_0', 'switchcos_1', 'switchcos_2'], bounds={'switchcos_0': (0.0, 0.35), 'switchcos_1': (0.0, 0.35), 'switchcos_2': (0.0, 0.35)}), name='switchcos_1', latex_label='switchcos_1', unit=None),\n",
       " 'switchcos_2': __main__.prior_switchcos(dist=custom_prior_switchcos(names=['switchcos_0', 'switchcos_1', 'switchcos_2'], bounds={'switchcos_0': (0.0, 0.35), 'switchcos_1': (0.0, 0.35), 'switchcos_2': (0.0, 0.35)}), name='switchcos_2', latex_label='switchcos_2', unit=None)}"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mix_model.set_prior(priors)"
